<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3577] AbstractReaderSource.getLine always returns null when no Janitor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3577</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying to read the source code out of a SourceUnit. The API has this method declared:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.codehaus.groovy.control.io.ReaderSource.getLine( int lineNumber, Janitor janitor );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which is implemented in AbstractReaderSource.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The API/doc says that Janitor is optional, and the code does let you pass a null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if you do pass a null janitor then the function always returns null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The method is trying to return a field named &apos;line&apos;, but if the janitor is null then cleanup() is called, and line is set to null, so the method always returns null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll submit a patch myself in the next few days. It is easy to write a test for. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
